column1633: In January of 2010 I went to the local bar with a few of my shipmates.  We were all drinking and dancing and having fun.  After a while I went to the bathroom.  I didn't really notice but  Admiral John Doe had followed me  inside the bathroom.  He locked the door and pushed me up against the wall.  He told me that this was a Petty Officer initiation and he forced me to give him oral sex.  He said that If i told anyone he would ruin my career.  I was crying and he ordered me to stop.  He put one hand over my mouth and pushed me against the wall of the bathroom and raped me.  He said that I better not tell anyone and even if I did, no one would believe me.  It was horrible.  I was terrified that he was really going to hurt me so I did as I was told.  When he finished he left the bathroom.  I washed my face and went back to the bar.  I waited until everyone left together because I was afraid to leave alone.  I never told anyone and I didn't go to the hospital because I was afraid that he would find out.
column1699: I was physically injured but too afraid to seek medical attention due to threats.
